-I'm well, thank you.
-Good, how was your flight?

42
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:49,720
It was good. Mum,
I swear you look younger every time

43
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,760
Oh please stop lying to your mother.

44
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:54,240
[Charlie laughs]

45
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:56,600
This is my friend, Keme. Keme, my mother.

46
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,440
-Hello, honey how are you?
-Good thank you

47
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:01,840
-Good to see you.
-This is Josh, and Teni. Guys, Keme.

48
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:04,680
Josh, nice to meet you.
I've heard a lot about you.

49
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,760
Well, welcome to our home. Shall we go in?

50
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,960
-[Keme] Thank you.
-It's good to see you, honey.

51
00:02:09,038 --> 00:02:11,840
-[Keme] Ohhhhh
-[music]

52
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,440
-Come in
-[laughter]

53
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:17,320
-Hey honey, see who’s here.
-Welcome home, son.

54
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,280
-It's so good to have you back son.
-It's good to see you, dad.

55
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:22,960
Ehhhhh!

56
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:26,880
Keme, come in, come in,
come in. Come meet my dad.

57
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,400
Dad, this is my friend, Keme.

58
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,920
-Keme.
-Nice to meet you.

59
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,160
[Mum] Have a seat.

60
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:34,880
[Dad] My dear,
get them something to drink.

61
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,320
Oh I will, yes.

62
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,720
Darling, go in there and get…

63
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,800
I got you your favorite meat pie.

64
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,840
-Yes!
-Get the meat pies and drinks.

65
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,960
-[Mum] I know you're going to love it.
-Keme

66
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,160
You’re in for a treat, man

67
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,360
My mum makes
the best meat pies in the world.

68
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,640
-Yea?
-Oh that's right, Charlie.

69
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:53,000
Your mother is a perfect cook.

70
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,720
You know she gets the basic ingredients,
and then creates magic

71
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,200
Haha, that's how I created this.

72
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,960
[laughter]

73
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:03,680
-[Charlie] Lollipop!
-[Lollipop] Oh my God!

74
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,200
[Charlie] How are you?

75
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,280
Ahhhh-ahhhh

76
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:09,440
-[both] It's so good to see you.
-[Charlie] Jinx!

77
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,880
-How are you?
-I'm okay

78
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,640
Now, you're squeezing the life out of me!

79
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,120
[Lollipop] Sorry.

80
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:19,000
So, okay, meet my friend, Keme.
My sister, Lola.

81
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,400
-Hey.
-Hi.

82
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,040
Nice to meet you.

83
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,720
Nice to meet you too, Lola.

84
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,600
[footsteps] [Temi] Meat pie.

85
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,920
[Keme] Oh okay.

86
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:34,000
-[Mum] That's it, very good
-[music]

87
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:36,840
Alright.

88
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:42,120
At least we can use this as
refreshment before... dinner is ready.

89
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,400
-[mum clears throat].
-[Teni] D'you want some juice?

90
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,360
[Charlie] This smells fantastic

91
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:48,760
No, no, no, no, just serve them.
They are the visitors [laughs]

92
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,880
Ohh, well, I'll serve my son.

93
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,240
Awww, mom.

94
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:56,280
-[Charlie] Thank you Mama.
-You're welcome.

95
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,440
And me.

96
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,120
Please don't forget me.

97
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,400
[laughter]

98
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,560
-[plates clinking]
-[phone rings]

99
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,120
So how are the wedding plans going?

100
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,840
-[Teni] So far, so good
-[Joshua] Yeah

101
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,839
Okay. Yes, That’s fine.

102
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,800
That’s fine, thank you so much.

103
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:21,320
Yea, alright. God bless. Bye.

104
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:23,120
-Hey, easy.
-Oh sorry. Hi

105
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:26,000
Hi, I wasn't expecting to
bump into anyone.

106
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,720
-Are you leaving?
-No no.

107
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:31,600
Not at all. I was wondering what
was keeping you out here.

108
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,760
So I came to check on you.
Make sure you were safe.

109
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Alright, just kidding.
I wanted to stretch my legs

110
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,680
and I noticed you hadn’t
had some of the famous pie

111
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,280
and no drink either,
so I brought you some.

112
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,560
You do know stale
food can make you sick, right?

113
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:49,680
Okay, thanks for the nutrition lesson.
Are you a doctor?

114
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:53,120
No, not even,
just a concerned friend, I guess.

115
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,160
Right.

116
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,400
You gonna take it or what?

117
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,120
Oh yes, yes, sorry.

118
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,920
-Thanks. Yes.
-Yea?

119
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,960
-No pie?
-I had to…

120
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,280
-No [chuckles]
-Okay.

121
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,120
I had to step out to make a phone call.

122
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,280
The call must have been important.

123
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:09,280
-Yes it was.
-Was it business?

124
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,120
Do you usually ask these
many questions of people you just met?

125
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:18,240
The thing is, Charlie talks about you,
like, all the time.

126
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,600
So, in my mind, we're already friends.

127
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,400
Friends. [smacks lips]
There’s that word again.

128
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,600
Do you have a problem being friends?

129
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,880
-No comment.
-No... [sighs]

130
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:31,840
Spoken like a true lawyer.

131
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:35,760
Oh, wow. Okay, fine,
Charlie has really spoken about me a lot.

132
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,800
What about you? What do you do?

133
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,320
Err, this and that…

134
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,480
Alright, I'm an investment banker.
[inhales]

135
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,200
-I work on Wall Street.
-Wow.

136
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,400
You know I was thinking you were like...

137
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:50,720
-an actor or model or something like that.
-[chuckles]

138
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,800
Sorry, I didn't mean to laugh,

139
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,000
but you think i could pass for an actor?

140
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:59,320
What is it? My eyebrows,
or my perfect leading man looks?

141
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,440
Which one?

142
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:03,720
[sighs] Uhmm..

143
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:06,680
I’m gonna go back inside, okay?

144
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,680
[sucks teeth] Sure.

145
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:16,200
I’m hoping you're gonna get
to stay home a lot longer this time.

146
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,400
I hope so too.

147
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:20,400
-Hi, Lollipop.
-Oh, there you are. [clears throat]

148
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,720
I was beginning to
wonder where you guys went to.

149
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,520
-I needed to use my phone, to call, just--
-[Keme coughs]

150
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,240
[exhales]

151
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,440
[Keme] Right.

152
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,320
[mum chuckles]

153
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,680
[Charlie] Everything okay?

154
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:36,280
[lighthearted music]

155
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:44,760
Ejike! [door closes] How are you doing?

156
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:48,800
Mum, can you try knocking once in a while?

157
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:50,360
It's that thing that p…

158
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,680
[sucks teeth]

159
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:55,000
Come in mum, good morning.

160
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,840
make yourself comfortable.

161
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,640
[sniffs]

162
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,040
Did you sleep well?

163
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,560
I did, actually.

164
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:09,880
[sniffs] How was your night?

165
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:12,200
We thank God.

166
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,960
Your father called this morning,

167
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,600
but it was too early,
so didn't want to wake you up.

168
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,560
He was expecting your call last night.

169
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,800
Right, I actually meant to call him.

170
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:26,520
Sorry, I got in really late
last night and I was really tired.

171
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,640
-I'm going to Abuja.
-Okay.

172
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,120
You’re home,

173
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,160
I want you to come with me.

174
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,120
I will be fine

175
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:38,360
And besides, Charlie and I actually
have a couple of meetings here, so

176
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,360
next weekend.

177
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:46,120
And when are we going to get to meet
this your mysterious friend?

178
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,400
You'll meet him soon.

179
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,480
We're just a little
busy right now, that's all.

180
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,720
Hmm

181
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:57,920
Okay, so it's more
important to have these meetings

182
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:02,120
with your mysterious
friends than go and visit your father?

183
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,960
I did not say that, alright?

184
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,400
Okay, so when you finish
with your meetings, come to Abuja.

185
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,680
Okay. What's going on?

186
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:17,080
Come on tell me, why are
you so intent on me coming to Abuja,

187
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,000
What's happening?

188
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,760
Is it a bad thing to
go and visit your father?

189
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:21,800
No of course not.

190
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,640
But you literally just said,
he's busy doing his political stuff.

191
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,480
So why do i need to be there so badly?

192
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:30,000
-Okay.
-Okay.

193
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,920
Stay for your meetings.

194
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:36,520
I mean... [laughs]
You never listen to what I say.

195
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,159
Here we go.

196
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,679
I really don't know why I bother!

197
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:41,960
Okay, look. Mum, mum, mum!

198
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:44,080
Where are you going? Goodness.

199
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,960
Okay.

200
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:49,080
Okay, look, let's do this.

201
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,880
We will spend this weekend together

202
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,960
We will do some fun stuff
then you can go to Abuja on Sunday.

203
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:56,480
And when I'm done with
my meetings here, I...

204
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,480
I will come join you.

205
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,560
That's a good idea.

206
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:06,320
Oh, and I know the perfect place
to take you.

207
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,640
-Ohh!
-Oh dear Lord.

208
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:11,480
-This will be fun. [laughs]
-What did I get myself into?

209
