00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:25,880
[female voice] Good morning,
Brother Ejike.

220
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:29,920
I hope you are
enjoying your trip to Nigeria.

221
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,760
So far, so good. How far?

222
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,800
You are looking good.
Tunde is taking really good care of you.

223
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:39,720
Hmm! That one? Do I even get to see him?

224
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,640
He is always off to one
political thing or the other.

225
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:45,800
That's a good thing because it means
politics is actually working out for him.

226
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,560
Hmmn, well yes.

227
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,600
I guess he’s trying
to be like your father.

228
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:52,440
Hoping one day to become Senate President.

229
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:54,760
Yeah, that would be something.

230
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,560
But look, listen

231
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,680
I just had like the weirdest
conversation with my mum.

232
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,560
She’s trying a little too
hard to get me to go to Abuja.

233
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,360
I feel like there’s
something else going on. What is it?

234
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,400
Why do you think so?

235
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,480
Hey, come on, we both know that woman.

236
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,800
She doesn’t do anything for no reason.

237
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:14,160
-What's going on?
-[laughs]

238
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:16,520
Ah, I don't know.

239
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,640
-Come on.
-Come to think of it.

240
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,840
Maybe she wants to find you a wife

241
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:23,880
as you’ve refused to bring one home.

242
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,960
[Keme laughs]

243
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,880
-You guys are trying to find me a wife?
-Hmm-mmn

244
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,240
I can find a woman by myself.
Thank you so much.

245
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:33,640
Okay, then you better
hurry up and bring one home.

246
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:36,320
You know Aunty does
not take "No" for an answer.

247
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:39,280
Yeah, I can't even
deal with you guys, alright?

248
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,440
-I will see you later.
-Okay.

249
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:43,000
[grunts]

250
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,120
Don't bother coming to Abuja again.

251
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,640
He won’t even consider it.

252
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,040
Perfect.

253
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,080
Don’t worry about it.

254
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,480
I'll bring him over to Abuja next week.

255
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,600
-We'll see you there.
-[female voice ] Hello, Aunty.

256
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,400
Hello yourself.

257
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:08,400
Nma, haven’t I told
you to stop sneaking up on me?

258
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:12,360
I didn't sneak up on you.
I walked leisurely in.

259
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:15,840
[long hiss]

260
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:21,200
Did you see Sisi Toyin
when you picked up Kemi?

261
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,240
Uhhm no,
it was really early in the morning,

262
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,080
so she might have
been sleeping when I got there.

263
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,640
I didn't go upstairs, so I don't know.

264
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:29,120
Oh, that's okay.

265
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:32,920
I... guess I’ll call her later.

266
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,280
I can't make Bible study today.

267
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,440
I'm sure she wouldn't mind.
I mean she knows Charlie's around, so...

268
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:42,480
-Oh, speaking of Charlie,
-hmm-mm

269
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:45,560
His friend seemed like a... nice boy.

270
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,600
Yeah, he is.

271
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:52,080
I saw the way he was looking at you.

272
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:55,480
Mum, don't start jumping the gun now.

273
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:59,200
I'm not jumping the gun, and I’m
not saying anything that I didn’t see.

274
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:03,640
All I'm saying is,
I saw the way he was looking at you

275
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:08,080
and I bet you anything,
he’ll be here soon enough.

276
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,480
I'm sure he will be here soon enough, mum.

277
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,920
I mean, Charlie is his friend.
So yes, he will come back.

278
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,960
That is not what I meant, but never mind.

279
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:19,240
Trust me, he’ll be back.

280
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:22,960
Mum, you know I'm not
looking for a relationship right now.

281
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:26,920
All I want to do is focus
on God and my career, that's it.

282
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,800
Hmmn

283
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:33,760
Honey, you do
realize you’re only saying that

284
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:38,240
because... you haven't met the right
man yet?

285
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:42,560
When you do,
just like I did meet your father,

286
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:46,040
-Hmmm?
-Everything will fall into place.

287
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,320
You don’t have to be single to serve God,

288
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,240
you can serve him while married.

289
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:53,680
I did, and so are
countless women out there.

290
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:59,520
All you have to do is just
open your heart to the will of God.

291
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:02,200
<i>All you have to do is just open your heart</i>

292
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,600
<i>to the will of God.</i>

293
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,080
-Oh, stop.
-[laughs]

294
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,760
Ok mum, I've heard you.

295
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:17,080
["I Hear Say Dem Talk" playing]

296
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:31,320
You’ve literally been on your phone
since I got here, is everything okay?

297
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:35,080
Ah, I’m tired,
my cousin promised to call me

298
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:37,720
for a business proposition I made to him.

299
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,320
Oh, is this the cousin
you were telling me about?

300
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,480
The one that’s in the States?
When am I meeting him?

301
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,840
You’ll meet him soon.
He's quite busy at the moment.

302
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:46,480
He and one of his friends are
trying to set up

303
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:52,600
venture capital for businesses in
Nigeria, he can impact lots of Nigerians.

304
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,720
Wow! That is such a strange coincidence.

305
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,720
Charlie and his friend are
literally doing the same thing.

306
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,800
-Really?
-Yes. Maybe we should introduce them.

307
00:14:58,880 --> 00:14:59,720
What do you think?

308
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,880
Probably after
Teni’s wedding or what do you think?

309
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,560
Yes, that’s a good idea.

310
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:08,880
So, what does Charlie's friend look like?

311
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,240
He's hot. Very hot.

312
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:15,680
Well, do I smell an attraction?

313
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:19,440
Kemi, am I not
allowed to just admire someone

314
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,760
without you thinking
that there is something there?

315
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:23,320
Okay, now give me the details,
full details.

316
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,720
I want to listen.

317
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:28,280
Well, he did make
a really good first impression.

318
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,640
Hmmph!

319
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:35,480
[male voice] <i>Gala gala</i>
["I Hear Say Dem Talk" playing]

320
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,040
<i>&lrm;gala gala</i>

321
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:46,240
[Keme] This is ridiculous, man!

322
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:48,840
It's like the one thing
about Lagos that never changes

323
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:51,760
You know we've been here for…
Look at that, we've been here for an hour.

324
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:55,640
And we’ve moved I’m pretty sure
about five meters. It makes no sense.

325
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:57,000
You would think that after all this time,

326
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,320
the government would
have figured out new modes of

327
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,760
transportation to ease
the congestion on the roads

328
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:03,520
-[phone chimes]
-Hold on

329
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:09,200
Err, ok, Pastor Ben just
confirmed our meeting

330
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,920
-So we’re good to go.
-Oh, awesome, awesome.

331
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,240
What about the Centre for Law
and Business? Any word from them?

332
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,480
Oh no, they confirmed yesterday

333
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:17,400
so we have two meetings lined up now.

334
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,640
-Great.
-Yeah, man

335
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:19,600
‪[knock]‬

336
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:25,960
[in pidgin] Sir,
please buy from me, buy, please.

337
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,160
-How much?
-[hawker] 100 Naira each, sir.

338
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:30,840
[Keme] Do you want something?
I'm not really hungry.

339
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:33,720
[Charlie] It's fine, I don’t mind.

340
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,240
-Let me ask you something.
-[Hawker] Okay, sir.

341
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,600
-Did you go to school?
-No, sir.

342
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:39,920
-[in pidgin] You never went to school?
-Yes.

343
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:41,480
How come?

344
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:45,120
[in pidgin] Sir, no money …
Look at my beards

345
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:48,440
[in pidgin] I haven’t eaten
since morning, sir. Please buy, please.

346
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:50,120
Do you have any Naira on you?

347
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,920
No, unfortunately not.

348
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,560
Err, hold on,
I should have some change somewhere.

349
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:57,240
Okay, just give me one.

350
00:16:57,320 --> 00:17:00,400
[in pidgin] Emeka, bring a paper bag
for me.

351
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,560
-It's fine, keep the change.
-God bless you. Sir, thank you so much.

352
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,319
‪Emeka!‬

353
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,640
‪So what's this mystery man’s name?‬

354
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,118
-Keme.
-Keme?

355
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:24,520
Keme, sounds romantic. Lola and Ke--

356
00:17:24,598 --> 00:17:28,280
Kemi! There is no by Lola and Keme or Loke

357
00:17:28,358 --> 00:17:29,960
or whatever happening, please.

358
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,720
Okay, it’s fine.

359
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,920
So what’s happening tomorrow morning?
Are we still on for the market?

360
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,880
Yes we are. Bright and early,
so you need to be ready.

361
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,640
-So set your alarm.
-[sighs]

362
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:41,760
But Lola, please, why can’t Teni

363
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:45,000
just hire a professional wedding planner?

364
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,720
I don’t have to wake up
every weekend for this please.

365
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,840
Kemi, why are you complaining?

366
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,080
-You know, you like it.
-I don’t.

367
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,400
[laughter]

368
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:55,520
So how did it go at the market?
I hope you got all you wanted.

369
00:17:55,600 --> 00:18:00,040
Oh yes, we did.
Lola has such an eye for beautiful stuff.

370
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,720
Must you give Lola so much credit?

371
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:08,680
You are as talented as she is,
if not more.

372
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,640
It's okay, mum,

373
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:14,400
I am confident in my abilities

374
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:18,400
and I do not have a problem
with recognizing how gifted Lola is.

375
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:25,400
But mum, where is this coming from?

376
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:29,320
I'm just tired of "Lola this, Lola that",

377
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,240
you deserve some credit too.

378
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:37,120
Ok, thanks for looking out for me,
mum, but I am super cool with Lola.

379
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,760
[laughs sarcastically]

380
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,720
I don't know how you can be.

381
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,840
After the stunt she pulled with Femi.

382
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,400
-She ruined your engagement.
-Oh come on, mum

383
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:49,480
we both know it wasn’t Lola's fault.

384
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:52,600
Femi is such a horrible person

385
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,480
Lola did nothing wrong.

386
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,560
Well, that’s not how I remember it.

387
00:18:56,640 --> 00:19:01,240
It's fine, but I think we’ll...
agree to disagree then.

388
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:05,720
[car engines revving]

389
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:16,680
[door opens and closes]

390
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,680
-[Charlie] I'm sorry.
-What happened?

391
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,600
I'm sorry, sorry, I’m just coming.

392
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:23,800
The traffic in this town is... terrible

393
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,560
Third mainland was blocked.

394
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:30,120
We had to go through Yaba and Eko bridge.
Thank God for Lola who knows all the ways.

395
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:33,080
Well then, how is... Lola?

396
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,920
She's great, I suppose.

397
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:41,240
Yes, definitely.
Your sister is, she is something else.

398
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:45,040
Yea, I think so too.

399
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,080
Why do you sound like that?

400
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:51,120
Why do you have
that look on your face, Keme?

401
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:56,800
Alright, fine, fine.
Since we're here and we’re doing this

402
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:01,400
Yes, I've been actually
meaning to talk to you about this.

403
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:05,240
-Hmmn...
-I know it's kind of weird, but I like her

404
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,160
As in, I really like her.

405
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:10,400
You think she would
agree to go on a date with me?

406
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,800
Why don't you ask her?

407
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:14,080
Wait, you are actually cool with this?

408
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:16,200
No, I'm not.

409
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:19,640
-Oh my bad.
-[laughs] I’m just kidding, come on.

410
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,320
I can't think of nobody better.

411
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,360
[clears throat]

412
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:27,240
Hey man, I appreciate this, seriously.

413
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,720
-[chuckles]
-No, seriously.

414
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,160
-It means a lot to me.
-No problem, no problem.

415
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:33,160
-I won't let you down.
-Oh, no <i>wahala</i>.

416
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,880
-Let's get to business.
-Alright.

417
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,880
We are ready to see her now,

418
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,760
if you can just give her a ring.
Tell her we're here.

419
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,200
[in Yoruba] Iya Dundun.
Please, let me have

420
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:46,080
three wraps of amala, and meat.

421
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:48,840
-[Iya Dundun] Okay, how many meats?
-Uhmm...

422
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:52,040
Two each. Make it goat meat and beef,
okay?

423
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:53,840
Any <i>ponmo</i>?

424
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:57,440
These ones are <i>ajebo</i>,
they can’t eat <i>ponmo</i>, just--

425
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:01,040
No, no, no, I will
have some <i>ponmo</i>, thank you very much.

426
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,400
-[laughs]
-Why not?

427
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:04,280
Mehn, how's the…

428
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,840
-Thank you.
-[Charlie] Thank you, man.

429
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,440
How’s the wedding planning going?

430
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:11,520
-Maaan! It’s going good
-Yes.

431
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:13,400
I learned something very early on.

432
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:14,960
[Keme] What’s that?

433
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:16,560
The wedding belongs to the bride.

434
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:20,440
I simply do as I'm
told and we’re all happy.

435
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:22,280
So I hear.

436
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,320
And Lola is doing an amazing job.

437
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:24,560
Of course, she’s amazing.

438
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:26,440
I don’t know how she finds the time

439
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:28,040
to do all the things she gets to do.

440
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:32,200
It’s like she can out plan
any event planner in the world.

441
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,960
-[Charlie] That's crazy.
-I tell you what?

442
00:21:34,040 --> 00:21:36,840
I mean, all of her creativity and style,

443
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,640
-Simple, but classy.
-Classy, yes.

444
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:41,720
she just seems like
that kind of person, you know?

445
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,680
She’s just that kind of person,
that's all.

446
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:47,040
-Hmm!
-Hmm!

447
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,840
Why do you have that look on your face?

448
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:51,600
Hey, you think we didn’t see how
you were staring at her the other night?

449
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,480
Are you guys being serious right now?

450
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,000
I can’t say someone is incredible anymore,

451
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:57,640
I can’t just
compliment your sister in peace.

452
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:01,920
-[Josh] this is the food, let's dig in.
-Yes good idea.

453
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:07,680
So?

454
00:22:11,520 --> 00:22:12,680
I could actually get into this.

455
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:15,120
-It’s actually pretty nice.
-[Keme] Not bad at all.

456
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,160
The amala is soft,
the soup tastes really delicious.

457
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:20,440
-[Charlie] It's pretty good, actually.
-Hmm!

458
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,480
Iya Dundun is the best.

459
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:27,320
So, guys, this is my business idea.

460
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:32,880
[In Yoruba] Joshua, <i>buka</i>?

461
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:35,160
You want to open a <i>buka</i>?

462
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,400
Listen up guys.

463
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,680
It is a bukateria par excellence.

464
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:41,240
[sighs]

465
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:44,960
What I’m trying to do is
blend the local traditional <i>buka</i>

466
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:49,240
with the modern-day fast food joint.

467
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,880
-That could actually work.
-Yeah.

468
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:55,600
Ah, who do we have here?

469
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:59,080
Ehhhh!

470
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:00,600
[Lola] Hello.

471
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:03,920
-Awww, how are you?
-I'm fine, thank you.

472
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,240
-How are you?
-I'm fine.

473
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,680
-Good to see you.
-Same here.

474
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:07,600
How are you?

475
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:10,760
-I’m okay.
-Good. Business is looking good.

476
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:12,000
-Thank you.
-Well done.

477
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:14,040
Thank you, thank you.

478
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:15,680
Ah, Auntie Lola!

479
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:18,560
Efe, I didn't know you were in town now.

480
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:20,480
-How are you?
-I’m fine o, I’m fine.

