I'm so sorry, baby.

1726
01:22:12,520 --> 01:22:14,120
I am so sorry.

1727
01:22:17,400 --> 01:22:19,480
I prayed so hard.

1728
01:22:20,800 --> 01:22:24,120
And then God sent me Charlie and Keme.

1729
01:22:24,680 --> 01:22:26,080
Praise God.

1730
01:22:28,360 --> 01:22:30,280
Why would anyone do this?

1731
01:22:30,360 --> 01:22:31,640
Why?

1732
01:22:31,880 --> 01:22:33,520
Oh honey, I love you.

1733
01:22:33,600 --> 01:22:35,440
I love you too, mom.

1734
01:22:36,200 --> 01:22:37,120
It’s okay.

1735
01:22:39,120 --> 01:22:42,480
I’m just grateful
that God brought me back to you.

1736
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:44,400
So am I.

1737
01:22:44,640 --> 01:22:45,960
[groans]

1738
01:22:46,080 --> 01:22:48,120
It's okay, don't try to move.

1739
01:22:50,480 --> 01:22:52,600
Don't touch it,
don't touch it, Just leave it…

1740
01:22:59,000 --> 01:23:01,480
[Keme's dad] Ah,
here comes the prodigal son.

1741
01:23:01,560 --> 01:23:06,000
Look at you, moping around
the house because of a woman,

1742
01:23:06,640 --> 01:23:10,760
instead of sealing a simple family deal.

1743
01:23:11,120 --> 01:23:12,200
[mum] You know, I don't even know

1744
01:23:12,280 --> 01:23:15,760
how we'll face the disgrace of yesterday.

1745
01:23:16,360 --> 01:23:18,240
We were at Otunba's last night,

1746
01:23:18,320 --> 01:23:21,720
discussing the wedding
plans and he was so angry

1747
01:23:21,800 --> 01:23:25,280
that you couldn’t even bother to...
show up.

1748
01:23:26,320 --> 01:23:31,600
It took all the skills
I possess to pacify him and his daughter.

1749
01:23:32,600 --> 01:23:34,200
How could you do that to us?

1750
01:23:34,280 --> 01:23:37,520
It will be a wonder if
Otunba speaks to me again.

1751
01:23:37,600 --> 01:23:39,040
[dad] I don't know what got into him,

1752
01:23:39,120 --> 01:23:42,080
what possessed him,
he even went as far as telling Wande

1753
01:23:42,160 --> 01:23:44,480
that... he is breaking up with her.

1754
01:23:45,480 --> 01:23:46,600
Can you imagine?

1755
01:23:46,680 --> 01:23:48,760
[chair squeaks]

1756
01:23:48,840 --> 01:23:50,000
-What is that?
-What is this?

1757
01:23:50,080 --> 01:23:51,240
Look at it

1758
01:23:53,880 --> 01:23:55,000
What's it?

1759
01:23:56,800 --> 01:23:57,960
That is the woman that I love.

1760
01:23:59,920 --> 01:24:02,480
The woman that I'm going to marry, right?

1761
01:24:03,760 --> 01:24:06,680
Beaten up, kidnapped,
tortured … Because of you?

1762
01:24:07,360 --> 01:24:09,640
Did...

1763
01:24:09,720 --> 01:24:11,840
-Did you ask them to beat her--
-No!

1764
01:24:11,920 --> 01:24:13,800
I didn't ask anybody to beat her.

1765
01:24:14,360 --> 01:24:17,200
All i said was
that they should keep her until--

1766
01:24:17,280 --> 01:24:18,600
[Keme groans] Mum!!!

1767
01:24:18,680 --> 01:24:23,280
Until I could convince you that she had
asked...

1768
01:24:23,360 --> 01:24:25,400
you to leave her alone.

1769
01:24:25,920 --> 01:24:28,600
I wouldn't ask anybody to beat her.

1770
01:24:29,280 --> 01:24:32,920
-I didn’t--
-What's wrong with you people?

1771
01:24:34,080 --> 01:24:35,400
Who does this?

1772
01:24:37,440 --> 01:24:42,200
Dad, I'll send every single copy--

1773
01:24:42,280 --> 01:24:43,520
-Wait, wait, wait.
-of these photos.

1774
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:45,320
Dad, dad, please, please,

1775
01:24:46,240 --> 01:24:49,440
These pictures are going out,
okay? Unless you do what I say.

1776
01:24:51,080 --> 01:24:54,520
If you don’t, let's see how
your whole vice-presidential ambition,

1777
01:24:54,600 --> 01:24:55,520
let's see how far that goes for you.

1778
01:24:55,600 --> 01:24:57,880
You want to ruin me, me, your own father?

1779
01:24:57,960 --> 01:24:58,800
Me, ruin you?

1780
01:24:58,880 --> 01:25:00,080
Your own blood?

1781
01:25:00,160 --> 01:25:03,360
Dad, you kidnapped someone!

1782
01:25:03,920 --> 01:25:05,120
Look!

1783
01:25:07,040 --> 01:25:09,280
Mum, dad, her parents
have been worried for days,

1784
01:25:09,360 --> 01:25:10,880
wondering where their daughter is.

1785
01:25:10,960 --> 01:25:12,000
Not knowing whether she's alive or dead

1786
01:25:12,080 --> 01:25:16,240
and I am supposed to be
worried about your... re... reputation.

1787
01:25:16,320 --> 01:25:18,560
your career,
that’s what is important right now?

1788
01:25:18,640 --> 01:25:20,320
What do you want us to do?

1789
01:25:20,400 --> 01:25:23,080
How about we put this
whole marriage charade to an end?

1790
01:25:23,400 --> 01:25:25,960
Can we do that? I am not marrying Wande.

1791
01:25:29,160 --> 01:25:31,280
I need you to
apologize to Lola and her family.

1792
01:25:31,840 --> 01:25:34,440
Mum, I'm being serious.

1793
01:25:36,240 --> 01:25:38,840
Ok, and dad, the people who did this,

1794
01:25:39,760 --> 01:25:40,760
I need them arrested.

1795
01:25:40,840 --> 01:25:42,000
[mum laughs]

1796
01:25:42,080 --> 01:25:46,080
I will never apologize to anyone

1797
01:25:46,160 --> 01:25:47,920
for looking after my family.

1798
01:25:49,440 --> 01:25:53,560
Ok, let's see how
you will enjoy... jail then.

1799
01:25:53,640 --> 01:25:55,920
Hey, hey, hey, stop bluffing there.

1800
01:25:56,400 --> 01:25:59,080
Ejike, now listen, let me tell you.

1801
01:25:59,880 --> 01:26:04,520
No security organization
in this country,

1802
01:26:04,600 --> 01:26:06,960
I repeat, in this country,

1803
01:26:07,040 --> 01:26:11,400
that will put, my wife and I
in jail! Do you hear me?

1804
01:26:11,480 --> 01:26:12,960
Alright, dad.

1805
01:26:13,880 --> 01:26:16,040
Let's put that to the test. Shall we?

1806
01:26:17,240 --> 01:26:19,320
Since you are the big man. Right?

1807
01:26:19,720 --> 01:26:21,320
Maybe you’re a big man here.
But let's see what happens

1808
01:26:21,400 --> 01:26:23,480
when they face pressure
from the international media.

1809
01:26:24,560 --> 01:26:26,560
Yes, because maybe you guys didn’t know,

1810
01:26:26,640 --> 01:26:29,920
but... Lola is a British citizen.

1811
01:26:31,160 --> 01:26:33,320
So let's see what
happens when the news gets

1812
01:26:33,400 --> 01:26:35,920
a story about a British
citizen being kidnapped, beaten

1813
01:26:36,000 --> 01:26:37,760
and almost killed in Lagos.

1814
01:26:39,040 --> 01:26:41,280
Let's see how that goes,
Maybe that will be a story then.

1815
01:26:43,200 --> 01:26:45,040
What?

1816
01:26:45,520 --> 01:26:46,520
-[Ms. Chukwuemeka] Dele.
-Ma.

1817
01:26:46,600 --> 01:26:48,680
What happened to
the girl I asked you to hold?

1818
01:26:48,920 --> 01:26:52,800
Err... Uhhm...

1819
01:26:53,560 --> 01:26:56,600
Mr... Ejike... came and saved her.

1820
01:26:56,680 --> 01:26:59,320
<i>Ehnehn</i>, and I’m
just hearing about it this morning?

1821
01:27:01,480 --> 01:27:04,960
I... had no... credit, ma'am.

1822
01:27:05,040 --> 01:27:06,080
And then I sent--

1823
01:27:06,160 --> 01:27:07,560
Shut up your mouth!

1824
01:27:08,280 --> 01:27:11,240
I pay you enough money to make sure
there's enough credit on your phone

1825
01:27:12,360 --> 01:27:15,080
How can I ask you to do something
and you just disappointed me?

1826
01:27:15,160 --> 01:27:19,160
I didn't... disappoint... you.
I didn’t, Ma.

1827
01:27:19,240 --> 01:27:21,120
It's Mr. Ejikeme, ma

1828
01:27:21,200 --> 01:27:22,200
It was Ejike who came--

1829
01:27:22,280 --> 01:27:25,160
If you had done your job,
he would not have found her.

1830
01:27:25,240 --> 01:27:27,040
How did he know where to look?

1831
01:27:27,800 --> 01:27:30,480
Ah, eh eh!

1832
01:27:30,560 --> 01:27:33,200
Insider information, I'm sure.

1833
01:27:33,280 --> 01:27:35,480
Oh, that's
your excuse for not doing your job?

1834
01:27:35,560 --> 01:27:37,160
Insider information.

1835
01:27:37,920 --> 01:27:39,720
No, no, wait, wait, wait.

1836
01:27:39,800 --> 01:27:41,000
Who beat her up?

1837
01:27:41,080 --> 01:27:42,760
-Beat her?
-Yes.

1838
01:27:42,840 --> 01:27:44,240
[both] Who beat her up?

1839
01:27:44,320 --> 01:27:45,320
-[Dele] Beat her?
-Yes.

1840
01:27:45,400 --> 01:27:48,280
I didn't beat her. It wasn't me.

1841
01:27:48,360 --> 01:27:50,520
-You don't know?
-No, sir.

1842
01:27:50,600 --> 01:27:54,760
You were asked to watch
and keep an eye on someone

1843
01:27:54,840 --> 01:27:56,720
and you’re telling me you don't know who?

1844
01:27:56,800 --> 01:27:58,360
Do you know how serious the issue is?

1845
01:27:58,440 --> 01:28:01,840
I know, sir. I didn't beat her.
[in Yoruba] True! No sir.

1846
01:28:01,920 --> 01:28:03,160
-Dele!
-[Dele] Ma.

1847
01:28:03,240 --> 01:28:04,320
How often have I told you

1848
01:28:04,400 --> 01:28:06,400
that you must always tell the truth?

1849
01:28:06,480 --> 01:28:08,400
I’m speaking the truth.

1850
01:28:08,480 --> 01:28:11,080
Ok, let me tell you exactly what happened.

1851
01:28:11,560 --> 01:28:13,480
I had running stomach.

1852
01:28:14,440 --> 01:28:15,480
Yes, Ma.

1853
01:28:15,560 --> 01:28:18,160
My stomach was making noises.

1854
01:28:18,240 --> 01:28:19,520
[Dele] So I ran to the toilet

1855
01:28:19,600 --> 01:28:21,400
and before I came back,

1856
01:28:21,480 --> 01:28:22,760
the girl had vanished.

1857
01:28:23,080 --> 01:28:27,160
It's... my stomach, ma'am.

1858
01:28:27,240 --> 01:28:28,160
You know what?

1859
01:28:28,240 --> 01:28:32,320
Deal with them,
ask Kunle to handle this issue.

1860
01:28:32,400 --> 01:28:35,520
I have to clean up all
this before It gets to the press.

1861
01:28:35,600 --> 01:28:36,920
-Please, sir
-I'm off to see Otunba

1862
01:28:37,000 --> 01:28:38,400
to tell him our own version

1863
01:28:38,480 --> 01:28:40,640
of the story before
he hears it from somebody

1864
01:28:40,720 --> 01:28:41,800
-Do you hear me?
-Good idea.

1865
01:28:41,880 --> 01:28:42,880
Deal with them

1866
01:28:42,960 --> 01:28:45,000
-No, as for you
-It's...

1867
01:28:45,080 --> 01:28:46,960
-you've lost your job.
-It's running stomach--

1868
01:28:47,040 --> 01:28:48,080
-No, ma, it's not me.
-And you,

1869
01:28:48,160 --> 01:28:51,240
I'm going to lock you up.
I will lock you up.

1870
01:28:51,320 --> 01:28:53,800
How could you have
let that happen to that girl?

1871
01:28:53,880 --> 01:28:57,120
I said, "Hold a girl,"
and you end up beating her

1872
01:28:57,200 --> 01:28:59,600
until she is totally unrecognizable.

1873
01:28:59,680 --> 01:29:01,080
[Lola's mum] Where is she?

1874
01:29:01,160 --> 01:29:02,600
Where is the spineless coward

1875
01:29:02,680 --> 01:29:04,640
who had thugs beat my daughter?

1876
01:29:06,120 --> 01:29:08,880
-You?
-Who is this woman?

1877
01:29:09,920 --> 01:29:11,400
-Dele, get rid of her.
-Ma?

1878
01:29:11,480 --> 01:29:13,640
-Out!
-If you touch me,

1879
01:29:13,720 --> 01:29:16,240
I will tear you to pieces this morning.

1880
01:29:16,320 --> 01:29:18,240
You dare hide behind your thugs?

1881
01:29:18,320 --> 01:29:19,560
Face me!

1882
01:29:19,640 --> 01:29:21,120
Face me like a woman!

1883
01:29:21,200 --> 01:29:25,040
So I can show you what it is
when cowards think they are above the law.

1884
01:29:25,120 --> 01:29:29,240
Madam, leave my
house before I get the police

1885
01:29:29,320 --> 01:29:33,000
to lock you up for trespassing.

1886
01:29:33,080 --> 01:29:34,080
The police?

1887
01:29:34,160 --> 01:29:37,280
After what you did to my daughter?

1888
01:29:37,360 --> 01:29:39,240
Lock me up?

1889
01:29:39,520 --> 01:29:41,680
You dare touch me one more time,

1890
01:29:41,760 --> 01:29:43,880
and I will show you why
they say that Nneka Chukwuemeka

1891
01:29:43,960 --> 01:29:47,560
is worth more than ten men. Your daughter
had bitten off more than she can chew

1892
01:29:47,680 --> 01:29:48,520
How dare you?

1893
01:29:48,600 --> 01:29:49,680
-Aunty, let's go.
-[Ms. Chukwuemeka] Rubbish

1894
01:29:49,760 --> 01:29:51,440
I'm begging you.

1895
01:29:51,520 --> 01:29:52,880
Ok guys take her inside.

1896
01:29:52,960 --> 01:29:55,640
What kind of a mother are you?

1897
01:29:56,440 --> 01:30:00,560
You would rather see your son unhappy

1898
01:30:00,640 --> 01:30:03,160
because of your political goals?

1899
01:30:03,240 --> 01:30:05,960
You don't know what you're talking about.
Get out of my house!

1900
01:30:06,040 --> 01:30:08,440
Take her inside. Stop! Take her inside!

1901
01:30:08,920 --> 01:30:10,440
What kind of woman is this?

1902
01:30:10,520 --> 01:30:12,000
I know I know, please, alright?

1903
01:30:12,080 --> 01:30:13,440
Oh my God.

1904
01:30:13,520 --> 01:30:14,560
Take her inside.

1905
01:30:14,640 --> 01:30:15,760
Get out!

1906
01:30:21,240 --> 01:30:22,760
Ah, get out!

1907
01:30:23,000 --> 01:30:24,720
[in Yoruba] Are you deaf?

1908
01:30:25,080 --> 01:30:26,680
[in yoruba] She asked you to leave

1909
01:30:28,720 --> 01:30:30,840
Ah, madam!

1910
01:30:35,040 --> 01:30:36,840
[sighs]

1911
01:30:50,880 --> 01:30:52,000
Let me see.

1912
01:30:57,280 --> 01:30:58,600
Congratulations.

1913
01:30:59,360 --> 01:31:01,600
I hope you are at
least happy with yourself.

1914
01:31:03,160 --> 01:31:04,440
Uhmm, I...

1915
01:31:05,920 --> 01:31:08,920
I can’t even recognize the person
seated in front of me right now, honestly.

1916
01:31:09,000 --> 01:31:11,240
Ejike, please.

1917
01:31:12,800 --> 01:31:15,720
Don’t look at me like that,
I am not a monster.

1918
01:31:18,120 --> 01:31:21,720
I’m doing the best I can for my husband.

1919
01:31:23,960 --> 01:31:27,040
Look, I didn't mean to hurt Lola.

1920
01:31:28,000 --> 01:31:29,200
Things just got out of hand.

1921
01:31:29,800 --> 01:31:31,520
Yes, but mum, but I kept telling you

1922
01:31:31,600 --> 01:31:34,360
I kept telling you I did
not want to marry Wande

1923
01:31:34,440 --> 01:31:36,920
it wasn’t complicated.
Why wouldn’t you just listen?

1924
01:31:38,600 --> 01:31:43,640
Mum, I love you, okay?
Always have, always will.

1925
01:31:43,720 --> 01:31:46,440
But I can't have
you interfering in my life like this.

1926
01:31:46,520 --> 01:31:48,800
It’s just not gonna work.

1927
01:31:49,240 --> 01:31:50,400
I'm sorry.

1928
01:31:53,640 --> 01:31:56,000
I won’t interfere anymore.

1929
01:31:58,160 --> 01:31:59,240
Forgive me?

1930
01:31:59,320 --> 01:32:01,360
It’s just one more thing.

1931
01:32:04,040 --> 01:32:07,680
I actually need you to go and
apologize to Lola and her family.

1932
01:32:07,760 --> 01:32:10,760
Mum, not one of those
manipulative apologies you give,

1933
01:32:10,840 --> 01:32:12,840
when you don’t want people to sue you.

1934
01:32:13,560 --> 01:32:16,320
I need a genuine one, okay?

1935
01:32:17,040 --> 01:32:18,560
For me, please.

1936
01:32:19,200 --> 01:32:21,080
I need you to help me make this right.

1937
01:32:22,320 --> 01:32:26,560
I need you to help me keep
the woman that I actually love.

1938
01:32:28,760 --> 01:32:29,800
Alright.

1939
01:32:31,320 --> 01:32:35,280
Well, I'll apologize, I'll grovel,

1940
01:32:35,360 --> 01:32:39,480
I'll cry to bring
the smile back in your eyes.

1941
01:32:41,200 --> 01:32:42,160
Are we good now?

1942
01:32:44,600 --> 01:32:47,640
There’s just... one more thing.

1943
01:32:48,200 --> 01:32:49,480
God, what now?

1944
01:32:50,600 --> 01:32:56,400
I need you to promise to rededicate
your life to Jesus.

1945
01:32:56,480 --> 01:32:59,280
Ejike, I don't know
what you're talking about.

1946
01:32:59,360 --> 01:33:01,720
My faith in God is just fine,

1947
01:33:01,800 --> 01:33:04,000
I am very active in church.

1948
01:33:04,560 --> 01:33:07,840
[laughs] How did
you come up with this ridiculous idea?

1949
01:33:09,080 --> 01:33:10,280
Mum, come on.

1950
01:33:10,920 --> 01:33:12,880
Let’s be serious here.

1951
01:33:12,960 --> 01:33:15,080
Not even you can
lie to yourself that much.

1952
01:33:15,680 --> 01:33:19,280
Surely, you know
that you’ve fallen so far from Him.

1953
01:33:20,040 --> 01:33:21,840
I mean, look at what your life has become.

1954
01:33:21,920 --> 01:33:24,160
Look at the things
you’re doing with your time.

1955
01:33:24,240 --> 01:33:25,840
Look at your face.

1956
01:33:25,920 --> 01:33:27,000
Who is this person?

1957
01:33:27,080 --> 01:33:30,040
What happened to that... prayer warrior?

1958
01:33:30,120 --> 01:33:32,320
You know, the one that raised me…

1959
01:33:32,400 --> 01:33:34,280
Mum, I became a Christian because of you,

1960
01:33:34,360 --> 01:33:36,280
You were my role model.

1961
01:33:36,600 --> 01:33:39,320
I wanted to be like
you, I wanted to have that relationship

1962
01:33:39,400 --> 01:33:42,080
with Christ the way you did.
I wanted to serve,

1963
01:33:42,160 --> 01:33:44,680
just because seeing you serve looked so…

1964
01:33:46,960 --> 01:33:48,520
I wanted to be like you.

1965
01:33:49,320 --> 01:33:52,040
How did you go from being that person to

1966
01:33:52,840 --> 01:33:54,720
whoever this is?

1967
01:33:54,800 --> 01:33:55,800
Son.

1968
01:33:58,280 --> 01:33:59,800
Politics is a beast.

1969
01:34:03,320 --> 01:34:08,200
You go in there with
high hopes of changing things,

1970
01:34:08,720 --> 01:34:12,400
of destroying the endemic corruption

1971
01:34:12,480 --> 01:34:15,520
that has paralyzed our country.

1972
01:34:18,880 --> 01:34:20,840
And before you know it

1973
01:34:21,720 --> 01:34:25,080
You’re making deals to
get things on your agenda done.

1974
01:34:26,560 --> 01:34:31,280
Very soon you realize that to survive

